description:
Superstar creator, David Finch took full creative control over Bruce Wayne's newest book, where he matches up against the more supernatural and horrific sides of his beloved home, Gotham City. See the Dawn Golden Case story arc page for more information.

The series only lasted five issues before being relaunched in The New 52 for a second volume. This was mostly due to delays on the part of Finch, who overestimated his ability to both write and draw the book on time, with artist Jason Fabok filling in for the final two issues.

Collected Editions

  • Batman: The Dark Knight: Golden Dawn
  • Batman: The Dark Knight Unwrapped By David Finch Deluxe Edition (#1-3)

For Post-Flashpoint Volume 2, refer to Batman: The Dark Knight.
name: Batman: The Dark Knight

description:
Originally called The Dandy and The Beano: Golden Years, this series launched in 1987 to celebrate the 50th anniversary of The Beano and The Dandy (in July 1988 and December 1987 respectively). With the 60th anniversary, the series title changed to Beano and Dandy: 60 Years and then in 2007 it changed to Beano and Dandy: 70 Years. In 2009 they finally made the name independent of any milestone, with the series being retitled Classic Beano and Dandy. There has been a new issue every year except 1988. Most issues only feature Beano and Dandy characters, but some include guests from other comics: Beezer, Topper, Nutty, Plug, Magic, Sparky, Victor, Bunty, Twinkle, and/or their annuals and summer specials have featured. 
 
List of issues: 
1987: The First Fifty Years 
1989: More From The First Fifty Years 
1990: Great Stories From The First Fifty Years 
1991: Fifty Years of Annuals 
1992: Famous Faces from the Comics 
1993: Magic Moments 
1994: Fifty Years of Fun 
1995: 101 Great Stories 
1996: An Alphabet of Fun 
1997: The Comics at Christmas 
1998: Around the World in 60 Years 
1999: Side by Side 
2000: A Library of Laughter 
2001: History of Fun 
2002: Funshine and Laughter 
2003: Favourites from the 40's 
2004: Focus on the Fifties 
2005: A Spin Around the Sixties 
2006: A Seventies Selection! 
2007: Crazy About Creatures 
2008: Comics in the Classroom 
2009: Winter Games 
2010: Heroes
